description:
Rosette Nebula is always my favorite object during the winter.  I just can't stop myself to slew the telescope to this Rose. We got about 8 days of the OK night sky during the first two weeks of January in the SF bay area. I was able to collect a reasonable amount of data.
Ha, OIII, and SII narrowband filters presented in the Hubble color palette plus the natural star color using R, G, and B filters.
Technical details:
Telescope: TEC 160FL + Astro-Physics 0.72x Quad Telecompressor Corrector
Mount: Astro-Physics Mach 2 GTO
Imaging cameras:ZWO ASI6200MM 
Software: PHD2, PixInsight, Lightroom 6.4, Sequence Generator Pro, Photoshop CS6
Location: Palo Alto, California, USA
